  "title": "BIM Modeler",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ol><li>Develop, maintain and update BIM models in accordance with project specification. </li><li>Produce coordinated construction drawings, shop drawings and detailed documentation that comply with the industry standards and regulations.</li><li>Collaborate closely with the stakeholders to incorporate design inputs into BIM models.</li><li>Prepare and manage documents, e.g., shop drawings, submission records, coordination logs.</li><li>Incorporate feedback and revisions accurately to support smooth project delivery.</li><li>Participate in meetings and discussions to support the project execution.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</li></ol><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ol><li>Diploma in Engineering / Architecture / Building or any related field.</li><li>Proficient in AutoCAD and Revit software.</li><li>Good understanding of construction detailing, drawings, and documentation processes.</li></ol><p><br />This position follows a 5.5 day work week and is site-based.</p>",
